item.title: Endometriosis Awareness, a comic by Lily Williams
item.description: Back when Imgur did the big content update about what was allowed on our private storage, my entire repository of uploads was wiped out, including my public posts. Don't care about that. I'd saved everything important and most of it was nonsense. Except for this one. This is important to keep up. I posted it last decade I think and people have probably posted it since then but more relevant than ever due to the wave of medical ignorance spreading and reversal of the progress made towards doctors not disregarding the suffering and experiences of their female patients. https://lilywilliamsart.com/portfolio/my-endo-story/

item.title: Awesome look into apology and accountability
item.description:
Gentleman made a slight at a video, caught some learning, explained without excusing, apologized with accountability. A change in direction is cooler to see than deflecting, excusing, minimizing. Not all disabilities are visible, and not all are apparent because we all have limited knowledge. We are learning everyday (hopefully). We can strive for everyone to be able to open bottles, however that looks like for us.
Bottle opener in question.
Visual on how mobility rings help us. Be kind, be better. Cheers

item.title: GovBrief Today #310
item.description: Welcome to the Trump Show, where the rest of us are bit players. After the Indiana House agreed to a gerrymandered congressional map, he published a list of nine state senators who "need encouragement" even though there have already been bomb threats and swatting. His Justice Department told prison rape auditors to stop enforcing protections for trans and intersex inmates in juvenile facilities, state prisons, and immigration detention. The law still exists. They just won't check if anyone's following it. His Defense Secretary excused 22 boat attacks that killed 87 people by saying Trump can use military force whenever he sees fit. The star changed into a tuxedo for a Saturday afternoon matinée. The Kennedy Center honorees clustered behind him at the Resolute Desk. A new season of The Apprentice, filmed on location in the Oval Office. At the Trump Show, he decides who gets raped, who gets killed, and who gets threatened.
